Baseball Sets Start Times for Wild Card Tiebreakers, ALDS Playoff Openers

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-09-28T04:34:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/baseball-sets-start-times-for-wild-card-tiebreakers-alds-playoff-openers.html
Major League Baseball  set starting
times for two possible wild card tiebreakers as well as the
opening games in the American League Division Series.  If the  Boston Red Sox  and Tampa Bay Rays finish tied after
the end of the regular season today, a one-game playoff for the
AL wild card spot will take place tomorrow at 4:07 p.m. at
Tropicana Field in St. Petersburg, Florida.  Later in the day at 8:07 p.m. eastern time, a one-game
playoff will take place at Busch Stadium in  St. Louis  to decide
the National League wild-card team if the Atlanta Braves and St.
Louis Cardinals finish tied.  The starting times for the Sept. 30 opening games in the
ALDS are set for 5:07 p.m. and 8:37 p.m. Eastern time.  The late game will feature the  New York Yankees  hosting the
Texas Rangers or Detroit Tigers. Boston or Tampa Bay will play
at Texas or Detroit in the 5:07 p.m. game.  The complete schedule for the division series will be
released at a later date, MLB said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  